    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix sequence number comparison in RLC UM entity\n\n### Summary\nThe RLC UM entity contains an inconsistency in sequence number comparisons that can lead to incorrect timer behavior when sequence numbers wrap around the modulus boundary. In the `check_t_reassembly` function, a comparison between `rx_next_highest` and `rx_next_reassembly + 1` was missing the modulo operation, causing the reassembly timer to be incorrectly restarted in certain edge cases.\n\nThis issue manifests as stalled RLC reassembly when sequence numbers approach the modulus boundary, leading to missing SDUs and degraded throughput. The problem is particularly noticeable in high-throughput scenarios with frequent sequence number wraparound.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_rlc/nr_rlc_entity_um.c`: Added missing `% entity->sn_modulus` operation in the sequence number comparison within `check_t_reassembly` function to ensure consistent modular arithmetic.\n\n"
}